task.summary:
Implemented parsing Expression trees from a string which is formatted using prefix notation, without parentheses.
TODO: Implement more default operators for lookup, and implement the ability to register custom operators in the lookup table. Also, implement translating a String from prefix to infix, to allow parsing of infix expressions.
Add comments ASAP.

Implemented parsing Expression trees from a string which is formatted using infix notation, with all parentheses.
TODO: Implement more default operators for lookup, and implement the ability to register custom operators in the lookup table. Also, implement translating a String from prefix to infix, or the other direction.
Add comments ASAP.

Restarted the project source, working from the abstraction down according to the logical requirements of the library instead of beginning with the particular application of mathematics. Fully commented the RewriteRule abstraction, based on the Pattern and Expression abstractions. Also wrote the basic abstraction for the Pattern and Expression interfaces, which each need more extensive comments and a valid implementing class.
Commented Pattern.java, and added a TODO relating to the structure of the classes; viz. determining whether Pattern should extend Expression.
Created and commented the PatternVariable class, used for matching arbitrary Expressions.
Created and commented PatternConstant, which requires something along the lines of an ExpressionConstant class to properly function.

Created a ConcreteExpression class, and corrected a comment in PatternConstant. Also added a few TODOs which suggest important structural changes to the code, and should be reviewed and resolved soon.
